    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="171" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <head>No. 171.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Robeson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-04-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 6,
                                        1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Since the letter to you from this
                                Department, of the 29th ultimo, relative to the abrogation of the
                                treaty between Great Britain and the Sultan of Zanzibar or Muscat,
                                this Department has been orally informed by Sir Edward Thornton, the
                                British minister here, that it is not the wish of his government to
                                have the whole of that instrument annulled, but only that provision
                                of the treaty by which the right to transport domestic slaves, by
                                sea, within certain limits of their own territory, was reserved. I
                                will consequently thank you to modify accordingly any orders which
                                have been or may be given by the Navy Department upon the
                                subject.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
